<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Party Leader Praises Ties With France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 12 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the Vietnamese
Communist Party Le Kha Phieu said here Wednesday that his country
highly values France's position in Europe and in the world and the
two countries' traditional friendship, Vietnam News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Meeting visiting French Senate President Christian Poncelet,
Phieu expressed his belief that the two countries' relationship
would be brought to a new high in the 21st century for the benefit
of the two peoples, peace, friendship, cooperation and development.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Poncelet said Phieu's upcoming visit to
France would be an important event as it will start a new phase of
development in France-Vietnam traditional relations.
</P>
<P>
He affirmed that France attaches high priority to its
relationship with Vietnam and expressed his hope to further
promote the friendship and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Poncelet held talks with Vietnam's National
Assembly Chairman Nong Duc Manh and met Vietnam's Vice President
Nguyen Thi Binh.
</P>
<P>
Poncelet began his official goodwill visit to Vietnam on
Tuesday at the invitation of National Assembly Chairman Manh.
</P>
</TEXT>
