<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Provides Fund to Ukraine for Closing Chernobyl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain will provide Ukraine with 10.
5 million pounds (17.32 million U.S. dollars) in aid to help
consolidate the protective structure over the No. 4 reactor at
Chernobyl nuclear station.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook on
Wednesday during his meeting with Ukrainian President Leonid
Kuchma, the Ukrainian Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Cook said that to close Chernobyl by the end of 2000 is one of
the common interests shared by Britain and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Cook expressed his support to Ukraine's
application for the membership of the World Trade Organization,
saying that it would promote the development of the trade
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Expressing Britain's welcome to Ukraine's initiative to
integrate with Europe, Cook said that Britain will increase its
investment in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting Kuchma said that the two sides had agreed to
set up standing working groups to deal with issues with regard to
cooperation between the two countries. The groups will report
directly to Ukrainian president and British Prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian Prime Minister Victor Yushchenko and Parliament
Speaker Ivan Plyushch also held talks with Cook.
</P>
<P>
Britain ranked second among European countries in terms of
investment in Ukraine, following the Netherlands, and is Ukraine's
third largest trading partner in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Cook arrived in Ukraine on Tuesday and will leave for London
Wednesday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
