<DOCNO> XIE20000413.0004 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Fu Upset at National Diving Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Three time Olympic champion Fu
Mingxia was upset by younger rival Guo Jingjing in the final of
the women's 3-meter springboard at the Chinese national diving
championships here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Guo is the current top women diver in China and she proved that
by performing flawless routines and collected a total of 640.30
points in the final, beating Fu to the second place with 618.90.
</P>
<P>
Fu suffered a poor score in her second dive and admitted she
did not perform well today.
</P>
<P>
"I did not dive well tonight. I lost to myself," said the 22-
year-old Fu, who had a two-loss record in her three encounters
with Guo.
</P>
<P>
Her only victory was in the China Open in Wenzhou last June.
</P>
<P>
Guo will be paired with Fu at the synchronized springboard
event at Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Early in the morning, Li Na and Sang Xue claimed the title in
the women's synchrony 10-meter platform while Xiong Ni and Xiao
Hailiang snatched the men's title on the 3-meter springboard.
</P>
</TEXT>
