<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgian Soccer Coach to Stay Until 2002 World Cup  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The head coach of the Belgian
national eleven will now stay until after the 2002 World Cup
tournament thanks to his flair that has uplifted the team.
</P>
<P>
Robert Waseige succeeded George Leekens last October after an
embarrassing 4-3 home defeat by Finland and was originally asked
to see the 2000 European soccer championship co-hosts through this
summer's event.
</P>
<P>
Waseige has now been awarded an extension of his contract for
some good performances of the "Red Demons" that have beaten Italy
3-1 away and held Euro 2000 co-hosts the Netherlands twice, 5-5
away and 2-2 at home.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian national team has so far played six warm-up matches
under the guidance of Waseige and it won two matches, drew three
and lost one, going 2-1 down to England away.
</P>
<P>
Belgium is scheduled to play Norway and Denmark, both away, as
its final tune-up before the European championship kicks off on
June 10 in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
The 2002 World Cup tourney will be co-hosted by South Korea and
Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
