<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador Presents New Coins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's Central Bank Thursday
presented the characteristics of the new fractional coins that
will replace the 5,000, 10,000, and 20,000 sucre bills.
</P>
<P>
These fractional coins will start circulating in the local
market in the next three or four months because of the Ecuadoran
economy dollarization.
</P>
<P>
The new coins characteristics were approved by President
Gustavo Noboa, and the symbols that will be represented in every
one of these fractional coins were defined.
</P>
<P>
Jose Luis Icaza, an official in the Cental Bank's managing
board and former foreign trade minister, announced at a press
conference that the 50-cent coin will have on its obverse the
faces of two children and will be called "Goodness."
</P>
<P>
The 25-cent coin will have on its obverse a humming bird, with
its wings spread and will be called "Liberty." The 10-cent coin
will be called "Truth," while the five-cent coin will have a snow-
covered mountain and a river, and will be called "Beauty."
</P>
<P>
The one-cent coin will have the relief of the American
continent.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Villagomez, BCE's Monetary Species Unit director,
confirmed that some 10 million U.S. dollar cent units will arrive
in Ecuador in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Villagomez said that the banks started to withdraw with more
frequency the dollars they have in their Central Bank accounts to
exchange them for sucres. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
