<HEADLINE> Zambian Councillor Calls for Stiff Punishment to Witches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has been
urged to make amendments to the witchcraft act to give stiff
punishment to witches and wizards, Zambia News Agency reported on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Zambian councillor Joel Ndala as saying that
the law as it stands is lenient with people practising witchcraft.
</P>
<P>
Sorcerers or sorceress should not be shown any leniency as they
are making the lives of the people uncomfortable, he said.
</P>
<P>
He warned that witchcraft cases would increase if the situation
is not checked by putting in place stiff penalties against those
proved guilty of such offences.
</P>
<P>
From time to time, one heard of a person who died from
mysterious illness or a suspected witch who had made some of his
family members insane or bewitched them and in some cases a
government institution which has been deserted by workers because
of witchcraft, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ndala said witchcraft exists especially in villages and is
reigning fear among some communities.
</P>
<P>
The sad part is that those practicing it even bewitched
innocent children, he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the government through the courts of law to impose
stiff punishment on those proved practicing witchcraft as a timely
warning to other wizards to stop the practice from spreading.
</P>
