tolerate confrontational politics based on religious and tribal
intrigues.
</P>
<P>
Speaking here at a function to commemorate Tanzanian late
president Julius Nyerere's 78th birthday, Mkapa said some elements
in the country are trying to drive a wedge among people using
their tribal and religious affiliation.
</P>
<P>
Such tendencies are what Nyerere fought against, Mkapa said.
"It was not an easy task for Nyerere to build a country free from
religious and tribal differences."
</P>
