prosperous future by instilling national unity, peace and love for
the future generation as Mwalimu (Kiswahili word for "teacher", a
respectful address for Nyerere) was always crusading should join
my government in discarding such misdeeds," he said.
</P>
<P>
He described Nyerere, who died of leukemia last October in a
London hospital, as an architect of Tanzania's independence. He
managed to unite the 120 tribes in the country and also
contributed to the forging of the union between Tanganyika and
Zanzibar, Mkapa said.
</P>
<P>
The commemorating function was also attended by Vice President
Omar Ali Juma, former President Ali Hassan Mwinyi and Maria
Nyerere, wife of Julius Nyerere. 
