<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals in Cyprus Increase This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The number of tourists arriving in
Cyprus in February this year increased by about 20 percent from a
year earlier, the Cyprus News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The number of arrivals covering all categories of travellers
reached 124,485, about 15 percent up compared to the same month
last year.
</P>
<P>
For the first two months of the year, arrivals of travellers
reached 232,107 compared to 205,743 in the same period in 1999,
recording a 12.8 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 percent of the tourists came from Britain, 12.3
percent from Germany, 5.2 percent from Greece and 3.3 percent from
Russia.
</P>
<P>
The overwhelming majority of tourist arrivals, 82.2 percent, was
from European Union countries.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is the main foreign currency earner of Cyprus, which
contributes 20 percent of the country's gross national product
(GNP). 
</P>
