<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Council Approves Blix's Working Plan for UNMOVIC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council Thursday approved the working plan by Hans Blix,
executive chairman of the United Nations Monitoring, Verification
and Inspection Commission (UNMOVIC) for the new weapons regime in
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The move came after the Security Council reviewed and
discussed Blix's report Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
In the report which was formally presented to the Security
Council early this week, Blix proposed the staff structure for the
UNMOVIC with strong experts and technical personnel rather than
political functionaries, an apparent bid to make it different from
the now defunct United Nations Special Commission (UNSCOM) and
encourage Iraq to cooperate with the new arms inspection regime.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the press, Robert Fowler, president of the
Security Council for the current month and Canada's ambassador to
the U.N., said the council members had reached agreement on the
report and would send a letter to U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan to inform him of the approval.
</P>
<P>
In his report, Blix recommended most UNMOVIC staff will be U.N.
employees, which would firmly place them under the U.N. Charter
rule and bars them from working for any other outside body.
</P>
<P>
Blix proposed to eliminate the post of executive deputy but set
up an executive assistant with less power.
</P>
<P>
On the role of the college of commissioners for the UNMOVIC,
Blix said they would meet at least four times a year to provide
professional advice and guidance for the UNMOVIC and the decision-
making would be his alone.
</P>
<P>
Blix stressed that the UNMOVIC, like the UNSCOM, has the right
to have immediate, unconditioned and unrestricted access to any
and all areas, facilities, equipment, records and means of
transport.
</P>
<P>
Blix said the flow of intelligence of the UNMOVIC must be only
one way and have regard only to matters of relevance to the
mandate of the UNMOVIC.
</P>
<P>
He also said the new arms regime's public information officer
will ensure that there will be single authoritative point of
contact with the media, Blix himself or someone authorized for him.
</P>
<P>
The UNMOVIC was created by U.N. resolution 1284 adopted last
December. U.N. arms inspection in Iraq has been suspended since
the U.S.-led military strikes against the country in December 1998.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has refused to accept U.N. resolution 1284, saying lifting
sanctions is the precondition for U.N. arms inspectors to return.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
