project as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the bridge began in March 1999 by the
Shanghai-based International Group of Economic and Technological
Cooperation in China.
</P>
<P>
The cost of the bridge was jointly undertaken by the Chinese
government which granted 50 million Chinese yuan (6.02 million U.S.
dollars) and the Yemeni government which provided 180 million rials
(1.2 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The three-layer bridge comprises an upper bridge, five meters
above the ground; an underground tunnel with four traffic lanes;
and the ground under the bridge for the traffic in the left
direction.
</P>
