<HEADLINE> FC Frankfurt to be Investigated over Financial Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- German first division side
Eintracht Frankfurt are to be probed by German soccer federation (
DFB) over their debts and could face relegation as a penalty.
</P>
<P>
The 1980 UEFA Cup winners have been summoned before DFB
licensing committee on Friday to explain their finances, which
include debts of $6.8 million.
</P>
<P>
The club, which needs $12.2 million to be safe, will explain
the financial position and efforts to find a new backer as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
If Eintracht do not pay their debts, they could be thrown out
of the first division. According to the German soccer regulation,
clubs that break rules limiting the level of their debts can be
docked points or can even be relegated. 
