<HEADLINE> BAR Driver Zonta Crashed at Silverstone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- British American Racing driver
Ricardo Zonta of Brazil was involved in a 300 kmph accident at
Silverstone at the corner where Michael Schumacher broke his leg
last year.
</P>
<P>
Zonta's car flipped into a grass area after smashing into a
tyre-barrier at Stowe Corner during testing for next week's
British Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
The area behind the barrier is a no-go area for spectators but
the incident could force Silverstone officials to make changes to
that corner of the Northamptonshire track before the race on
Sunday week.
</P>
<P>
Zonta escaped with just a cut finger following the accident
after his car lost one of its wheels and started rolling sideways
along the gravel before hitting the barrier.
</P>
<P>
Zonta's car was sent out of control after one of its wheels
came off along Hangar Straight. The team will not run again today
until discovering the cause.
</P>
<P>
Schumacher, who began testing at the track this morning for the
first time since his accident last July, immediately went to the
scene.
</P>
<P>
The German, who had smashed head-on into a barrier rather than
go in sideways, had said last weekend that he would check the run-
off area at Stowe anyway.
</P>
<P>
Denys Rohan, chief executive of Silverstone Circuits, said
after looking at video footage of the incident that he would
listen to any suggestions by the drivers. 
</P>
