<DOCNO> XIE20000413.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Embezzled Funds From Three Gorges Project Recovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Of the 473 million yuan (57
million US dollars) embezzled and misappropriated by officials in
the massive relocation project linked to the Three Gorges Dam
construction, 338 million yuan (41 million US dollars) has been
recovered, Xinhua learned from a special auditing contingent here
today.
</P>
<P>
From 1993 through 1999, the central government earmarked a
total of 17.68 billion yuan (2.1 billion US dollars) for the
resettlement of 220,000 residents who live along the middle
reaches of the Yangtze River, where the new dam will be built, an
auditor said.
</P>
<P>
Auditors have learned that the misuse of the relocation funds
started as soon as the project did.
</P>
<P>
Over the years, prosecutors in the project area have uncovered
138 cases involving 165 officials who misappropriated 31 million
yuan. The most serious instance involved 15.56 million yuan
pocketed by a single official.
</P>
<P>
The Commission for the Construction of the Three Gorges Dam
issued an order today that the 1998 tally of 473 million yuan in
misappropriated funds discovered by the National Audit Office be
returned to the relocation account in full by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
The commission also ordered all towns and villages located
within the project boundaries to make their financial accounts
public and to accept public supervision so that further losses
will not occur.  
</P>
</TEXT>
