<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails 10th Anniversary of Pudong's Opening (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily will publish a
commentary tomorrow to mark the 10th anniversary of the founding
of the Pudong New Area, Shanghai, in east China.
</P>
<P>
The development and opening of Pudong has "deepened reforms and
further opened up China to the outside world," according to the
paper.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping is quoted as saying during a visit in Shanghai
that although Pudong is a latecomer in the reform campaign, "I
believe it will surpass other economic zones in the country."
</P>
<P>
After 10 years of development, Pudong has witnessed fast
urbanization, taking the lead in developing a market economy, and
making consistent efforts to cooperate with international market.
</P>
</TEXT>
