CANBERRA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A sharp fall of Wall Street's
Nasdaq index overnight prompted a sell-off on the Australian stock
market Thursday with few blue-chips escaping.
</P>
<P>
The sell-off was felt deepest in the local technology sector
with major media and telecommunications stocks also falling.
</P>
<P>
However, financial services and other major old economy
companies were mostly stronger.
</P>
