<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Arrives at Paris Clinic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian superstar Ronaldo arrived
at a Paris clinic in Thursday afternoon after injuring his knee in
his comeback match against Lazio yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The Inter Milan striker, whose appearance at Wednesday's
Italian Cup final first leg lasted only six minutes before
crumbling to ground in agony, was here to see the specialist who
operated on his right knee four months ago.
</P>
<P>
The twice FIFA Footballer of the Year walked into the Pitie
Salpteriere clinic on crutches with his weight on his left leg. It
has been learned from sources close to Inter in Paris that the
hospital would probably keep Ronaldo under observation and
undergoing tests for several days.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo was stretchered off six minutes after coming on as a
second half substitute in yesterday's match, his first appearance
since his right knee operation on November 30. Lazio won the match
2-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
