<HEADLINE> Shimizu S-Pulse Wins Asian Cup Winners' Cup Semifinal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Shimizu S-Pulse scored a
4-2 penalty shoot-out win over Bangkok Bank of Thailand in Chiang
Mai on Thursday in the first semifinal match of the 10th Asian Cup
Winners' Cup tournament.
</P>
<P>
The two sides played to a goalless draw after regulation time,
with Bank dominating most of the game but failing to convert a
greater number of scoring opportunities.
</P>
<P>
A 30-minute extra-time period also went scoreless, setting up a
penalty shootout.
</P>
<P>
Shimizu will play for the championship on Saturday against the
winner of the other semifinal match, between Novbakhor of
Uzbekistan and Al-Zawra of Iraq, who were tied 1-1 after the first
half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
