<DOCNO> XIE20000413.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ministry Pleased with Employment for Graduates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Education said
today it was pleased with the report of high employment rates for
this year's 1.07 million college graduates.
</P>
<P>
Postgraduates and students from well-known universities are
being actively pursued by employers, Qu Zhenyuan, an official with
the ministry, said at a briefing here today.
</P>
<P>
University graduates are in great demand in developed provinces
and cities in eastern and coastal areas, but the need is far less
in the underdeveloped western region, Qu said.
</P>
<P>
Postgraduates are most sought-after, the number of students
with bachelor's degrees is equal to the employment needs, and the
supply of junior college graduates has exceeded the demand,
according to the official.
</P>
<P>
He said that job fairs on college campuses have been the main
venue for linking graduates with employers. Currently, 70 percent
of students meet their future bosses at these events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
