<HEADLINE> Armed Opposition Group Busted in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Iran said that its security forces
on Thursday smashed a group of members of the military opposition
Mujaheddin Khalq Organization (MKO) who infiltrated into Iranian
territory from Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Intelligence Ministry said that the MKO members were
identified and busted before committing any criminal acts, the
official Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Foreign currencies, different types of rifles and pistols,
grenades and fake documents were confiscated from the group, the
ministry said, without giving more details.
</P>
<P>
The MKO launched two mortar attacks in the Iranian capital of
Tehran in February and March, injuring a number of civilians.
</P>
<P>
The Iraq-based MKO was a main political group which had fought
against the former Iranian shah regime, but it was outlawed in 1981
due to sharp differences with the Iranian clergy regime.
</P>
<P>
During the past decades, the MKO launched various attacks on
Iranian interests inside and outside Iran. In retaliation, the
Iranian armed forces also bombed the MKO bases in Iraq several
times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
