<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Speaker of Israeli Knesset </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here Thursday that China cherishes its traditional
friendship and mutually beneficial cooperation with Israel and
appreciates the importance Israeli government attached to China.
</P>
<P>
"China would like to join hands with Israel to push forward the
mutually beneficial bilateral cooperation," Jiang said during his
meeting with Avraham Burg, speaker of the Knesset (parliament).
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the Israeli parliament should play a
positive role in promoting the Sino-Israeli ties.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the history, Jiang said that during the World War II,
Chinese people extended friendly hands to Jewish people, who had
suffered persecution of the Nazi Fascism, by kindly receiving them.
</P>
<P>
Living together, the Chinese and Jewish people forged friendship
and the traditional friendship of the two nations laid sound
foundation for the establishment and development of the bilateral
ties, he added.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his satisfaction with the progress of the bilateral
ties, saying that significant achievement has been made in the
cooperation in politics, trade and economy, science and technology,
agriculture and culture since the two countries forged diplomatic
ties in 1992.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Burg extended his warm welcome to Jiang, saying
that representatives of all parties in the Knesset were present at
Thursday's meeting.
</P>
<P>
He described China as an important country in the world because
of its long history, splendid culture, large population, vast
territory and its role in the international arena.
</P>
<P>
Israel would like to further the exchanges and cooperation with
China in the fields of economy, culture and agriculture, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Burg presided over a ceremony to welcome
Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Thursday, President Jiang also paid a visit to Yad
Vashem, or Holocaust Memorial, and paid respects to late Israeli
Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin at his grave.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived here Wednesday for a state visit to Israel.
</P>
</TEXT>
