<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher on Singapore Stock market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed higher on
Singapore Stock Market Thursday with the benchmark Straits Times
Index moving up 28.51 points to end at 2,163.9.
</P>
<P>
The total volume was 259.19 million shares worth 851.89 million
Singapore dollars (about 497.66 million U.S. dollars). Losers led
gainers by 167 to 123 with 241 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AirOcean continued to top the actives chart with 20.57 million
counters changing hands. It was followed by ST Engg which had 16.
71 million shares done. SingTel was the next with a turnover of 16.
56 million units.
</P>
<P>
PacCent led gainers of the day gaining 160 cents to close at 18.
2 Singapore dollars. DBS moved up 120 cents to finish at 23
Singapore dollars. OCBC, SPH and UOB each ended 50 cents higher at
12, 32 and 11.9 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day sliding down 320
cents to close at 45.5 Singapore dollars. Venture sank 160 cents
to finish at 22.4 Singapore dollars. Chartered ended 60 cents
lower at 12.8 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
