<HEADLINE> Seven killed in Sri Lanka's Musical Show Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were killed
and 67 others injured in a grenade attack on a musical show in
Eastern Province of Sri Lanka Wednesday, police here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred in a stadium in Trincomalee Town, 260
kilometers from Colombo, on Wednesday night when hundreds of
people had gathered there to watch the show, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The injured have been admitted to local hospital. At least 10 of
the wounded were in serious condition, hospital sources were
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately clear who was responsible for the attack
which came on the eve of the traditional new year.
</P>
<P>
However, police authorities have blamed Tamil rebels for the
attack. The rebels, who have been fighting against the government
for a separate Tamil state in the country, have made similar
attacks in the past several years.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka took on a festive atmosphere Thursday when the
majority Sinhalese and Tamils celebrate the traditional new year.
</P>
</TEXT>
