<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Australia's indigenous group
could give financial support to peaceful protests during the
Sydney Olympics, a senior Aboriginal leader said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Aboriginal and Torres Straight Islander Commission deputy
chairman Ray Robinson said the ATSIC board had agreed to back
peaceful protest marches during the Games.
</P>
<P>
