<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A limited number of Galatasaray
fans would be allowed to attend next Thursday's UEFA Cup semifinal
second leg at Leeds United, according to UEFA president Lennart
Johansson.
</P>
<P>
Johansson said an agreement has been made by the UEFA executive
committee of letting a restricted number of Turkey fans at the
match. UEFA will make their official verdict known on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Leeds United have called for Galatasaray fans to be banned from
the match amid security fears following the stabbing to death of
two Leeds fans in Istanbul last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
