<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese-American Aids Agriculture Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Gubang Yan, a Chinese-American
entrepreneur, on Wednesday donated 100,000 yuan (about 12,000 U.S.
dollars) from his Fuhui Charity Foundation to Yunnan Agriculture
College.
</P>
<P>
The donation is the foundation's annual aid to the college, the
only agriculture college in Yunnan Province, southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The 100,000-yuan aid program was launched last year, and more
than 60 students received scholarships from it this year, either
because of their academic records or financial need.
</P>
<P>
Yan established the Fuhui Charity Foundation in 1997 to aid
education in China's poor rural and ethnic areas.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Agriculture College has more than 4,000 students, about
80 percent of whom are from the countryside, and one out of four
of whom are from extremely poor families, according to college
administrators.
</P>
<P>
The government gives 93 yuan (11 dollars) every month to each
student at the college, and provides additional financial
assistance to 452 extremely poor students, they said.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Agriculture College is one of the 14 colleges in China
that receive annual funds from the foundation, and a total of 5,
000 Chinese college students have received their scholarships from
this source. 
</P>
</TEXT>
