<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Connects Major Power Grids in Developing Western Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China expects to complete the
connection of the country's major power grids nationwide by the
year 2020 in the course of sending power from its western region
to the eastern areas, a senior Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
A fast-growing economy has brought a new stage in power
industry development, said Zhou Xiaoqian, assistant president of
the China State Power Corporation. So far, China has developed six
large power grids connected by a total of 567,000 kilometers of
power transmission lines.
</P>
<P>
Recoverable hydropower resources in western China expect to
increase to 270 million kw, accounting for about 72 percent of the
country's total.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Power Station, which is under construction,
will connect major power grids in the country and provide power
for areas in central and north China.
</P>
<P>
In addition, thermal power production bases in Shanxi, Shaanxi
and Jiangxi provinces will ensure large power supplies for Beijing,
Tianjin, Tangshan, Baoding and other cities in northeast China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
