<HEADLINE> China Busy Preparing for Int'l Steel Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- "Steel 2000", a high-level
international symposium scheduled for May 7-11, is expected to
attract more than 200 domestic and foreign steel giants.
</P>
<P>
Participants include heads of China's seven largest steel
companies and steel associations from Japan, Germany, Russia and
other countries, said Wu Jianchang, chairman of the organizing
committee and also deputy director of the State Administration of
Metallurgical Industry.
</P>
