<HEADLINE> Shanghai Economy Enjoys Stable Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 13 (Xinhua)-- Shanghai scored 14.64 million
yuan in industrial output during the first quarter, up 12.2
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The city's exports totaled 5.04 billion US dollars during the
quarter, up 37.6 percent. Its imports rose 85.3 percent to 6.04
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales rose 8.9 percent to 42.44 billion yuan, an
increase of 8.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The retail sales price index dropped by 1.9 percent in the
first quarter while the residents' consumption expanded by 6.2
percent.  
</P>
