meters, up 51 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Import of paper pulp was 960,000 tons, up 51 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Import of iron ore were 16.97 million tons, up 45.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
China's import of industrial end-products in the first quarter
was worth 36.4 billion U.S. dollars, up 31.6 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
-- Import of machinery was 7.2 billion U.S. dollars, up 23
percent.
</P>
