</P>
<P>
-- Import of textile yarns and products were 2.7 billion U.S.
dollars, up 29 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Import of steel products was 3.29 million tons, down 8.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Import of nonferrous metals was 1.28 billion U.S. dollars,
up 49.7 percent.  
