<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councilor Meets Japanese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor Wang
Zhongyu met with Yohei Sasakawa, president and chief
representative of the Japanese side of the Sasakawa Japan-China
Friendship Fund, and his party here today.
</P>
<P>
Wang, also secretary-general of the State Council, had a
cordial conversation with the guests, who are here to participate
in activities marking the 10th anniversary of the establishment of
the Sasakawa Japan-China Friendship Fund.
</P>
<P>
The Sasakawa Japan-China Friendship Fund, jointly set up by the
China Association for International Friendly Contact and the
Sasakawa Peace Foundation of Japan in December, 1989, was designed
for promoting prosperity of both countries and world peace through
exchanges between the people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Sasakawa Japan-China Friendship Fund has so far helped
launch more than 200 programs in the areas of industry agriculture,
environmental protection, science, technology, education and
health. 
