<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Customs Seizes Smuggled Human Tumor Tissue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Customs recently
seized a batch of human tumor tissues and related human gene
materials illegally carried by a passenger leaving the country.
</P>
<P>
 An official with the State Human Gene Resource Management
Office said today that the Beijing Customs is investigating the
case and will punish the offender.
</P>
<P>
The official revealed that the case involved a Beijing-based
biotech firm, which tried to send the tissues to a foreign country.
</P>
<P>
A state regulation promulgated in 1998 stipulates that human
gene resources and related materials must apply for approval from
departments concerned before being sent out of China, and
violators shall be punished.
</P>
<P>
Chinese laboratories are engaging in human gene research.
</P>
</TEXT>
