<HEADLINE> Quality Problems Found in Wooden Furniture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A recent random examination
conducted by the State Bureau of Quality and Technical Supervision
showed that only 57.1 percent of the wooden furniture on China's
market was up to state standards.
</P>
<P>
The spot check, covering 91 varieties of furniture produced by
25 enterprises across the country, found that the qualification
rate for bedroom furniture was only 45.3 percent, and the rates
for bookcases, and dining tables and chairs were 64.3 percent and
40 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Serious problems were found in small and private furniture
producers and dealers. Among the 51 checked products from 14 small
furniture enterprises, only 41.2 percent were qualified.
</P>
<P>
The quality problems were mainly in the surface coating layer,
which affects the appearance and longevity of wooden furniture.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
