<HEADLINE> Macao Provides Better Services to Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to better services to
investors from outside, five foreign-funded projects have been
approved to set up in the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR)
of China in the first quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
The projects are related to shoe-making, consultation service
of trading and construction, manufacturing of magnetic disk and
pharmaceutical production, Lee Peng Hong, president of the Macao
Trade and Investment Promotion Institute (TIPI), said at a press
conference Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
