<HEADLINE> Finnish Foreign Minister Reiterates One China Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Finnish Foreign Minister Erkki
Tuomioja reiterated Thursday that there is only one China in the
world and that Taiwan is an inalienable part of China.
</P>
<P>
In reference to Taiwan's recent regional election, Tuomioja
told a press conference that Finland's stance on the Taiwan issue
has not changed and his country will stick to the One China policy
and regards Taiwan as a province of China.
</P>
<P>
Finland established diplomatic relations with China in October
1950, one of the first Western countries to do so, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Tuomioja stressed that China's entry into the World Trade
Organization is in the common interests of both China and the
European Union. He said the EU hopes to reach an agreement with
China on the issue as soon as possible. 
</P>
