<HEADLINE> McDonald's to Open Branch in China's Most Populous Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The world's fast food giant
McDonald's will open a branch in central China's Henan Province,
and gradually expand its business to China's northwest and
southwest markets.
</P>
<P>
McDonald's has signed a cooperation contract with Zhengzhou
Youyi (Commercial) Co. to set up Henan McDonald's Co., Ltd. in
this China's most populous province, which has a population of
some 93 million.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. fast food giant will bring its first investment of
five million U.S. dollars to this province in mid-April during an
international trade fair to be held here in the province.
</P>
<P>
McDonald's has chosen China as its important market for further
development in the year 2000, said Zhu Yuanhe, Vice-President of
McDonald's (China) Co., Ltd., who paid a visit to Henan recently.
</P>
<P>
Zhu believed that there would be a rosy picture for McDonald's
in Henan. McDonald's plans to open at least 30 restaurants in
seven cities in the province. The first restaurant is scheduled to
open in Zhengzhou, capital city of Henan, in July.
</P>
<P>
McDonald's is also considering setting up a distribution center
in Henan when the time is ripe. McDonald's purchasing people will
come to Henan to study the local cattle raising and other raw
materials processing bases.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yixiang, vice-governor of Henan Province, said that Henan
is a market with great potential and his provincial government
would create good conditions for bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
McDonald's has opened 25,000 restaurants in 119 countries and
regions since it opened its first one in the United States in 1955.
McDonald's has 257 restaurants in 17 provinces and municipalities
in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
