<HEADLINE> Telephones to Be Popular in Rural Area of Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province is
making effort to provide 98 percent of its 15,000 villages with
access to telephone by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the province has carried out a series of key
telecommunications projects to erect phone lines to 92.5 percent
of its villages.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial telecommunications department
official, by the end of the third quarter this year, the
provincial government will invest 60 million yuan (about 7.23
million US dollars) to open telephone service in 110 villages in
remote poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
"This will allow us to bring the economic developments as well
as technological priorities to most villages," the official said.
</P>
<P>
Although telecommunications in the province's urban areas have
experienced a booming era in recent years, the rural areas are
still rather backward, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
