<HEADLINE> Chinese University Joins Rolls-Royce Technology Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The North Western Polytechnical
University (NPU) in Xi'an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi
Province, has become the first Chinese institution to join a
partnership with Rolls-Royce.
</P>
<P>
Gordon Waddington, Rolls-Royce Director of Research and
Technology, said the two sides will launch another two-year
research program to investigate the internal cooling of high
pressure turbine parts. The project is intended to complement heat
transfer experimental work already in progress at Oxford
University on similar cooling configurations, said Gordon.
</P>
<P>
Research at NPU will be combined with research work at Rolls-
Royce and the Department of Engineering Sciences at Oxford
University.
</P>
<P>
Rolls-Royce and the NPU have been collaborating on gas turbine
heat transfer research since 1992, and cooperation demonstrates
Rolls-Royce's continuing commitment to heat transfer research in
China, added Gordon.
</P>
<P>
Rolls-Royce has established leading positions in civil
aerospace, defense, marine and energy markets. Its core gas
turbine technology has created one of the broadest product ranges
of aero engines in the world, with 55,000 engines in service in
over 150 countries. Customers include more than 500 airlines, 2,
400 corporate and utility operators.  
</P>
</TEXT>
