<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anti-Dumping Against ROK, Japanese Steel Products Takes Effect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China has implemented today
temporary anti-dumping measures against cold-rolled stainless
steel sheets imported from the Republic of Korea and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC)
said in an announcement that from today, all importers of cold-
rolled stainless steel sheets originally made in the Republic of
Korea and Japan, covering six taxable items, will have to hand in
a certain amount of cash as guarantee money to Chinese Customs.
</P>
<P>
The amount of guarantee money to be handed in should suit the
degree of dumping as determined by the preliminary ruling of the
Chinese authorities, according to the announcement.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary ruling jointly made by MOFTEC and the State
Economic and Trade Commission says dumping does exist, and has
resulted in substantial injury to relevant Chinese industries.
</P>
<P>
A MOFTEC announcement on June 17 last year said that China had
decided to begin an anti-dumping investigation into imported steel
sheets. Over the subsequent several months, MOFTEC and the General
Administration of Customs investigated the import trade, and the
State Economic and Trade Commission and other relevant Chinese
departments launched investigations into the damage done by
dumping. 
</P>
</TEXT>
