<HEADLINE> Landslides Increase in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) --The Ministry of Land and Resources
said in the past 10 years, nearly 10,000 people have been killed
by landslides in China.
</P>
<P>
Landslides have cost the country some 30 billion yuan (3.6
billion U.S. dollars) in economic losses annually.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 1,000 power stations and several hundreds of reservoirs
are threatened by landslides.
</P>
<P>
Landslides destroyed 50 reservoirs in southwest China's Yunnan
Province in the past decades.
</P>
<P>
Geological experts said that rapid economic growth and increase
of population have had a negative impact on the environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
