<HEADLINE> 5 Ugandan Policemen Killed in Cult Church Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of five policemen were
among over 500 cult members burnt dead in the Kanungu church in
southwestern Uganda on March 17, a police spokesman said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Police Spokesman Asuman Mugenyi told Xinhua in a telephone
interview that "four of them were retired and one was still in
service when the Kanungu incident happened three weeks ago".
</P>
<P>
He refuted a press report on Thursday's New Vision daily that
more policemen were feared dead in the tragedy. "This is a lie. We
know only five people in the police force were killed and no
others were believed to be involved in the fire," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan police have offered a reward of 12 million
shillings (8,000 U.S. dollars) for the arrest of the six main
leaders of the Movement for the Restoration of Ten Commandments of
God suspected of killing nearly 1, 000 cult members. 
</P>
