<HEADLINE> Knicks Beats Nets 91-89 in Overtime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Latrell Sprewell collected 21
points and Larry Johnson atoned for two late missed free throws by
playing tight defense on Keith Van Horn on the game's final play
as the New York Knicks beat New Jersey 91-89 in overtime Wednesday
night.
</P>
<P>
With Miami losing by 17 points at Detroit, the victory pulled
the Knicks back within one game of the Heat in the division
standings.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Ewing added 18 points, and Charlie Ward scored 13
points, seven rebounds and five assists. Van Horn led the Nets
with 32 points.
</P>
<P>
In Auburn Hills, Michigan, Detroit Pistons disposed of Miami
heat 90-73. Jerry Stackhouse scored 29 points as Detroit helped
its own playoff cause while hurting the Heat's division-title
hopes.
</P>
<P>
Miami was without Tim Hardaway, sidelined with a right foot
injury.
</P>
<P>
In Boston, Boston outclassed Orlando Magic 95-91. Danny Fortson
had a season-high 23 points and 14 rebounds as Boston hurt Orlando
's bid for the East's final playoff berth.
</P>
<P>
Antoine Walker had 15 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists for
the Celtics, who have won consecutive games following a 10-game
losing streak.
</P>
<P>
In Cleveland, Milwaukee defeated Cleveland 101-100. Ray Allen
made the second of two free throws with 4.9 seconds left to move
Milwaukee into a tie with Orlando in the race for the NBA's only
remaining postseason spot.
</P>
<P>
Sam Cassell scored 18 of his game-high 29 points in the second
half to spark Milwaukee.
</P>
<P>
In Charlotte, North Carolina, Charlotte Hornets overpowered
Atlanta Hawks 119-87. David Wesley scored 22 of his game-high 29
points in the second half and Charlotte held Dikembe Mutombo
without a shot en route to its 10th win in 12 outings.
