<HEADLINE> Shanghai Launches Agriculture Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Government of Shanghai in
eastern China can now provide agricultural information to local
farmers more effectively as an agriculture website on the Internet
has been launched here recently.
</P>
<P>
Concerned departments in Shanghai are publicizing the Internet
knowledge among farmers in the municipality's suburban areas, so
that more farmers can use the website www.shac.gov.cn, which is
open to all the country's information resources and markets.
</P>
<P>
Browsers can get 26 kinds of information including farming
advices, practical techniques and introducing investment available
at the website.
</P>
<P>
Local farmers told Xinhua that they want the website to tell
them what they should plant, how to plant, and where they can sell
their farm produce and the price. 
</P>
