<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Sets up Internet Security Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The committee, chaired by Chief Secretary to the Government
Abdul Halim Ali, would adopt measures to prevent misuse of
official information following the introduction of electronic-
government, he told reporters after a function here.
</P>
<P>
"Without guarantee of security, public confidence and
enthusiasm to embrace new technologies and adopt the electronic
system may be affected," he said.
</P>
<P>
Data thefts overseas, including that suffered by a United
States Internet company that suffered millions of dollars in
losses due to intrusion to its computer system, provided the
Malaysian government a good lesson to learn from, Abdullah said.
</P>
<P>
He said the recent spate of illegal withdrawals from Automatic
Teller Machines in the northern state of Pulau Pinang showed flaws
in the electronic system.
</P>
<P>
He said that once the Internet Security Committee got down to
business, the issue of drafting new legislation to deal with such
problems would be discussed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
