<HEADLINE> 28 Killed in Electric Wire Snap in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The tragedy occurred at Daltonganj in Bihar's Palamu district
when a flag staff carried by the processionists struck a high
voltage cable overhead, the PTI quoted local official sources as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The wire snapped under the impact and fell on a chariot in the
procession, which immediately caught fire, said the sources,
adding that while some died of burn injuries, others perished due
to electrocution.
</P>
<P>
Local police had confirmed 28 deaths, including 21 who died on
the spot, and injury to a few. 
