<HEADLINE> Pierce, Seles Enter Third Round at WTA Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Mary Pierce of France
and defending champion American Monica Seles defeated their
respective rivals in a women's tennis tournament in Amelia Island,
Florida, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Pierce spent just 50 minutes to beat American Tracey Singian 6-
1, 6-3 while Seles edged Israel's Anna Smashnova 7-6 (7-0), 6-0.
</P>
<P>
After eight months away from clay, Seles took control of the
match by winning all the points in the tiebreaker, then used just
16 minutes to finish off her rival in the following set.
</P>
<P>
In other action, unseeded Patty Schnyder of Switzerland beat No.
5 seed Sandrine Testud of France 7-6 (7-4), 7-6 (7-0) in a hard-
fought match.
</P>
<P>
