<HEADLINE> Stoltenberg Edges Larsson in Atlanta Tennis Challenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Australian Jason Stoltenberg,
playing his first tournament since the Australian Open, edged
third seed Magnus Larsson of Sweden 3-6, 6-4, 6-4 at the Atlanta
Tennis Challenge tournament on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nicolas Massu of Chile whitewashed sixth-seeded Sargis Sargsian
of Armenia 6-2, 6-3, advancing to the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Stoltenberg had a good start to this year, reaching the quarter-
finals in Adelaide and the final in Sydney. After a five-set loss
to Jonas Bjorkman in the first round of the Australian Open,
Stoltenberg decided to give his knee a break.
</P>
<P>
Stoltenberg has been one of the most successful players in this
tournament's history. He lost to Marcelo Filippini and Pete
Sampras in past finals.
</P>
<P>
20-year-old Massu is the sixth-youngest player in the top 100.
This is only his 10th ATP Tour event.
</P>
<P>
In other matches Wednesday, fifth seed Chris Woodruff of United
States, and seventh seed American Jeff Tarango won in the first
round while second seed Stefan Koubek of Austria and eighth seed
Andrew Ilie of Australia reached the quarter-finals.
</P>
