<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soeharto Banned From Traveling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
But a member of Soeharto's lawyers Juan Felix Tampubolon in an
interview with Xinhua Thursday morning said that his side has not
received any letter issued by the attorney's office in connection
with the decision.
</P>
<P>
"We have yet seen the letter. We just know from the media,"
Tampubolon said.
</P>
<P>
Director of Corruption Affairs, Chairul Imam said Wednesday
night that the travel ban was imposed in order to simplify the
investigation process, and his side has sent the letter to
Soeharto's family.
</P>
<P>
"The ban is to ensure that Soeharto could fulfill every summons
and be met with anytime," Imam was quoted by the Jakarta Post as
saying, adding that the restriction was made in anticipation of
news that Soeharto's family had planned to take the former strong
man abroad for further medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
Rumors had been rife that Soeharto's family had recently
applied for the U.S. visa and had bought a house in the U.S., the
Post quoted a source as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, Tampubolon disclaimed such rumors saying that the
rumors is created by the attorney's office to "legitimate the
imposition of the travel ban."
</P>
<P>
"We consider the ban as an overacting decision. Because as long
as we know, Soeharto has no intention to leave the country and
take medical treatment abroad," Tampubolon said.
</P>
<P>
Early this week, the attorney's office failed to question
Soeharto over his alleged involvement in corruption, collusion,
and nepotistic practices during his 32 years rule.
</P>
<P>
An independent medical team set up by the attorney' office
along with Soeharto's medical team observing Soeharto's health
condition in the course of investigation process, declared that
Soeharto was not in a good shape to face questioning.
</P>
<P>
They advised the prosecutors not to launch further questioning
as they were worried if Soeharto underwent investigation he could
fall in to stroke again for the second time.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors of the attorney's office early this month has
questioned Soeharto, but they didn't get sufficient information to
confirm suggestion that Soeharto committed abuse of power when he
still was in power. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
