<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 56 Dead in Philippine Ship Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA April 13 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-six people were confirmed
dead when a passenger sea vessel sank Wednesday night off the
coast of Jolo, Sulu province in the southern Philippines, a local
TV report said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the ABS-CBN television, the ill-fated ship,
heading towards Bakung, Tawi-tawi Province, sank 3.4 miles off
the coast of Jolo, Sulu province Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The TV report quoted police sources as saying that 79 survivors
of the ill-fated M/V Andajada were rushed to the Jolo General
Hospital for medical treatment after the accident.
</P>
<P>
The M/V Andajada is reportedly owned by a certain Teting
Malsharip from Zamboanga City.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the mishap has yet to be identified as the
Philippine Coast Guard and maritime police continue to fish out
dead bodies from the water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
