<HEADLINE> Macedonia, Belgium Discuss Bilateral Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Macedonian Defense Minister Nikola
Kljusev and his Belgian counterpart Andre Flahaut said Wednesday
in Skopje, capital of Macedonia, that the tension in Presevo,
Bujanovac and Medveda is not conducive to regional security and
stability, reports received here from Skopje said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian News Agency reported that during the meeting,
the two defense ministers said the two countries did not want to
see an escalation of tension in the three areas, no matter who is
responsible for causing the escalation.
</P>
<P>
They also stressed that the Macedonian and Belgian defense
ministries should strengthen further cooperation and sign a
cooperative agreement.
</P>
<P>
During the Belgian minister's trip to the country, Flahaut
visited the Belgian troops which are part of the NATO peacekeeping
force in Macedonia. 
