<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China Port City To Upgrade Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, an important port city
and industrial base in north China, has decided to upgrade and
optimize its industries in the coming five years.
</P>
<P>
Major goals are to give tertiary industry a more important role
in local economy, foster new pillar industries such as electronic
information, bio-engineering, medicine and new energy, restructure
the state-owned enterprises, and further improve economic
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Science and technology will greatly benefit the process.
According to an official source, this year new and high
technologies will produce at least 21 percent of Tianjin's total
industrial output.
</P>
<P>
Priorities will also be given to development of the city's
central business zone, life insurance, joint-venture insurance and
banking business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
