largest in NATO troops in Albania. Shqiponja Brigade, a composite
troop, will replace Friuli.
</P>
<P>
NATO has deployed large numbers of troops in Albania when it
launched air raid against Yugoslavia last year. Most of the troops
have left for Kosovo or returned home. But there are still one to
two thousand NATO servicemen stationed in Albania, providing
various kinds of support to NATO troops in Kosovo. 
