<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Up First Amylose Research Institute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China's first research institute
on technology of amylose products has been set up in this coastal
city of east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
With Yu Roumu, a famous nutritionist, as honored director, the
institute has invited a number of renowned scientists as its
advisers or researchers.
</P>
<P>
The institute has so far made a lot of research findings in the
fields of amylose products from mushroom, ginseng, gingko, longan
and halobios.
</P>
<P>
The institute, a privately-owned firm, has hosted a seminar on
amylose research and production recently, attracting dozens of
experts and scholars nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that amylose, a major substance controlling
cellular growing will play an increasingly important role in
health care. 
</P>
</TEXT>
