<HEADLINE> Chronology of Major Events in China-Indonesia  Relations since 1950 (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The following is a chronology of
major events in China- Indonesia relations since 1950 (2):
</P>
<P>
February 20 - 23, 1997 -- Chinese State Councilor and Defense
Minister Chi Haotian paid an official good-will visit to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
June 18, 1997 -- Chairman of the Supreme Audit Committee of
Indonesia J.B.Sumarlin visited China.
</P>
<P>
November 11, 1997 -- A delegation from the Supreme Advisory
Council of Indonesia, led by its Chairman Sudomo, visited China at
the invitation of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
November 23 - 29, 1997 -- Vice Chairman of the Standing
Committee of the China's National People's Congress (NPC) Wang
Hanbin led a delegation to visit Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
April 11 -13, 1998 -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan
paid a working visit to Indonesia at the invitation of his
Indonesian counterpart Ali Alatas.
</P>
<P>
August 3, 1998 -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan
addressed the issue of the ethnic Chinese and Chinese nationals
living in Indonesia when he attended the ASEAN Regional Forum
meeting in Manila and he also discussed the issue with Indonesian
Foreign Minister Ali Alatas. He expatiated that the status of the
ethnic Chinese should be respected, their personal safety and
legitimate rights and interests should be fully protected and they
should be treated the same as all Indonesian citizens.
</P>
<P>
November 17, 1998 -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met with
Indonesian President Jusuf Habibie in Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
May 8, 1999 -- Indonesian President B.Jusuf Habibie issued an
instruction to lift an almost three-decade-old ban on the use and
teaching of the Mandarin language and the discriminative
citizenship requirement for Indonesians of Chinese origin.
</P>
<P>
November 27, 1999 -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and Indonesian
President Abdurrahman Wahid had a meeting in Manila, where they
attended the 3rd ASEAN informal summit.
</P>
<P>
December 1 - 3, 1999 -- Indonesian President Abdurrahman Wahid
paid a state visit to China at the invitation of Chinese President
Jiang Zemin. During the visit, the two Presidents held productive
talks on bilateral relations and other major regional and
international issues of common interest and reached broad
agreement and understanding. Then China and Indonesia issued a
joint press communique.
</P>
<P>
January 22 -26, 2000 -- Indonesian Air Force Chief of Staff
Marshal Hanafie Asnan paid an official good-will visit to China at
the invitation of Lt. General Liu Shunyao, Commander of the Air
Force of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000413.0313 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chronology of Major Events in China-Indonesia  Relations since 1950 (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China and Indonesia mark the 50th
anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between
the two countries Thursday. The following is a chronology of major
events in China- Indonesia relations since 1950 (1):
</P>
<P>
April 13, 1950 -- China and Indonesia established diplomatic
relations.
</P>
<P>
October 30, 1967 -- The diplomatic relations between the two
countries were suspended.
</P>
<P>
July 3, 1990 -- Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen and
Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali Alatas signed in Beijing the
communique between Chinese and Indonesian governments on the
resumption of diplomatic relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
August 6 -11, 1990 -- Chinese Premier Li Peng paid an official
visit to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
August 8, 1990 -- The diplomatic relations between China and
Indonesia was resumed.
</P>
<P>
November 14 - 19, 1990 -- Indonesian President Mohamed Suharto
visited China.
</P>
<P>
June, 1991 -- Chinese President Yang Shangkun visited
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
April 10 - 12, 1992 -- Vice-President of Indonesia Y.M. Wapres
Soedharmono paid an official visit to China.
</P>
<P>
November 16 -19, 1994 -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin paid
his first state visit to Indonesia. During the visit, China and
Indonesia signed an agreement on promoting and protecting
investment and a memorandum of understanding on scientific and
technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
July 19 - 21, 1995 -- Foreign Minister of Indonesia Ali Alatas
paid an official visit to China at the invitation of Chinese Vice-
Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen.
</P>
<P>
March 13, 1996 -- Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali Alatas said
at a hearing of a Parliamentary Commission that the reunification
of China is an internal issue for the Chinese people and that
Indonesia will uphold its one China policy.
</P>
<P>
May 12 - 15, 1996 -- Chinese Vice Premier Zhu Rongji paid an
official visit to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
September 9 - 14, 1996 -- Chief of General Staff of Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA) Fu Quanyou visited Indonesia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
