<HEADLINE> Mideast Water Usage Protocol Signed in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Jordan, Israel and Palestine signed
in Como, Italy, on Wednesday an agreement on reasonable water
usage in the Mideast.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the three countries signed a protocol on
resolving the water problem in the area, which includes
desalinization installations and water re-cycling plants.
</P>
<P>
According to the protocol, a desalinization installation with
an annual capability of desalinizing 30 million tons of water will
be set up to relieve the water problem in the Amman area.
</P>
<P>
Water control officials from Palestine, Jordan and Israel also
welcomed foreign investments to these projects.
</P>
<P>
The three representatives signed the protocol after an intense
three-day negotiation promoted by the government and scientific
research institutions of Como. 
</P>
</TEXT>
