<HEADLINE> Xi'an Opens Comprehensive Art Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Shaanxi Art Museum, a large and
comprehensive museum combining exhibits and collections, opened to
public recently in Xi'an, the provincial capital of Shaanxi.
</P>
<P>
The museum, believed to be the first of its kind in China,
covers an area of 12,000 square meters and was created at a cost
of 28.78 million yuan (3.47 million U.S. dollars). It includes
exhibition halls and storage facilities, and was designed by the
renowned Chinese architect Zhang Jinqiu.
</P>
<P>
The museum is expected to play a positive role in promoting the
development of the province's art industry and cultural exchanges
with other countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
