<HEADLINE> Ningxia Launches Polio Immunization For Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- In a bid to achieve the country'
s goal of eradicating polio by 2000, northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region recently started an immunization campaign for 1.
05 million children under nine years of age.
</P>
<P>
In October last tear, polio was discovered in neighboring
Qinghai, which crippled a child. This was the first confirmed case
of polio in China for more than three years.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Health has launched a polio immunization
campaign in four areas in northwestern and western China --
Ningxia, Qinghai, Gansu and Tibet -- to contain the disease.
</P>
<P>
The local public health department aims to complete polio
immunization work by May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
