<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Zoo for Wild Animals in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Construction of northwest China'
s first zoo for wild animals has begun in the city of Wuzhong in
the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region with the approval of the State
Forestry Administration.
</P>
<P>
The zoo, to be built at a cost of 230 million yuan (about 28
million U.S. dollars), will cover an area of 667 hectares.
Construction will be carried out in three stages and the first
stage will be completed in three years. By then the zoo will have
more than 100 species of wild animals and plants.
</P>
<P>
It will be able to receive half a million visitors a year with
tourism income reaching some 30 million yuan (3.6 million U.S.
dollars) when it is completed in 2015.  
</P>
</TEXT>
