<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Stocks Down  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on the Sao Paulo
securities exchange, the largest in Latin America, closed down
Wednesday with the key Bovespa Index falling by 1.3 percent to 16,
323 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 32,735 million shares worth 864.44 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The stocks in Rio de Janeiro also closed down 1.1 percent at 57,
822 points. 
</P>
