<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close Down  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
closed down Wednesday with the benchmark IPC falling by 218.02
points, or 3.01 percent, to 7,016.69 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 75.569 million shares worth some 129.478
million U.S. dollars against Tuesday's 118.592 million shares
worth some 212.856 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican peso stood at 9.3925 to one U.S. dollar for sale
and 9.3860 for purchase from the Bank of Mexico, the Central Bank.
</P>
