<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Host Intl. Singing Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China will hosted a major
international vocal music contest from November 8-17 in this
capital of Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The ten-day event, the first of its kind in China, is aimed to
promote exchanges between music circles and develop the art of
vocal music, according to an official with the Ministry of Culture.
</P>
<P>
The panel of judges to be headed by well-known Chinese singer
Guo Shuzhen will include a dozen other artists from China, Romania,
the United States, Britain, Germany and Australia.
</P>
<P>
Singers between ages 18-32 worldwide are eligible to
participate in the contest, which will be jointly sponsored by the
Ministry of Culture and the provincial government of Guangdong,
the official said.
</P>
<P>
A number of prizes will be awarded, including one exclusively
for Chinese songs. The event will be held every two years in the
future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
