<HEADLINE> Shanghai Collects 100 Million Yuan in Interest Tax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China's largest economic center
has collected nearly 100 million yuan in interest tax since the
country introduced this tax last November.
</P>
<P>
The figure reached nearly 94 million yuan in the first quarter
this year, according to the latest official statistics.
</P>
<P>
While the introduction of interest tax is aimed at increasing
consumer spending, the savings deposits of Shanghai residents
still increased by 10.24 billion yuan in the first months of this
year, and their foreign-currency deposits also increased by 370
million US dollars during the two-month period.  
</P>
