<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drug Trafficking Discovered in Post Express Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Municipal Customs
Office recently discovered drug trafficking by post express
service for the first time.
</P>
<P>
About 3.1 grams of heroin were found between the packaging
paper and the box in a parcel sent from Seoul, capital of the
Republic of Korea, to Wangqing, a county in northeast China's
Jilin Province. The package was declared to contain only children
clothes.
</P>
<P>
Customs officials discovered the parcel during a routine
examination at a post express service bureau in Beijing, and the
case remains under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
