<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui to Speed Up Expressway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province will
invest 30 billion yuan to build seven expressways in the Tenth
Five-Year Plan period (2001-2005).
</P>
<P>
When work is completed, cars will be able to cross the province
in three hours from east to west, and in six hours from south to
north.
</P>
<P>
This will make Anhui an important passage linking the
economically advantaged Yangtze River Delta with western China,
which is now underdeveloped, but will be fully developed in line
with the decision made by the central government.
</P>
<P>
The seven expressways will connects Nanjing with Luohe,
Hangzhou with Xinyang, Nanjing with Jiujiang, Hangzhou with
Jingdezhen, Xuzhou with Xinyang, Shangqiu in Henan province with
Jingdezhen in Jiangxi province, and Shangqiu with Quzhou via Hefei
and Huangshan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000413.0339 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Personal Credit (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The lack of an efficient personal
credit system and effective methods to estimate personal credit
have become a main obstacle to the promotion of consumer credits
in China, according to the "Financial News".
</P>
<P>
On March 3, 1999, the People's Bank of China (PBOC) announced
that all Chinese commercial banks will have access to consumer
credit business.
</P>
<P>
Personal credit system enables people to conduct purchasing,
investing and managing activities on credit.
</P>
<P>
The healthy run of personal credit system usually depends on
the support of strong computer networks, a strong legal system,
and cooperation of other concerned government departments. In
western countries, consumer credit has covered 30 percent of all
credit services.
</P>
<P>
Commercial banks can decide whether or not to provide a person
with credit loans or mortgage concessions by calling out his
credit record according to his particular credit number.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000413.0340 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Personal Credit (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A complete personal credit system will greatly raise the
efficiency of taxation and financial services. But the lack of
knowledge about applicants' credit record seriously affects the
promotion of China's personal credit.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out that China's personal credit enterprises
need to advocate the real-name system for savings deposits and
financial assets, and set a credit record system.
</P>
<P>
On March 31 this year, China issued a regulation on adopting a
real-name system for individual bank accounts to protect the legal
rights and interests of the depositors.
</P>
<P>
The next step will be promoting the real-name system for
financial assets, and tax policies.
</P>
<P>
Another important precondition for establishing a personal
credit system is to have credit records of clients. But over-
strict credit terms has greatly discouraged Chinese people to set
up their own credit record.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out that a person who never borrows money will
never have any credit record. They suggest that credit card
services should provide larger overdraft lines, lower credit
interest ratios and interest-free terms to help Chinese people
borrow money on credit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000413.0341 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
