<HEADLINE> Chelsea Move up to Fourth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer club
Chelsea moved up to the fourth with a 2-1 victory over Coventry
City on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea, on a high after a 3-1 defeat of Barcelona in their
Champions League quarter-final first leg last week, went behind to
an 18th-minute goal from Coventry midfielder Gary McAllister in
wet conditions.
</P>
<P>
For a while Coventry, struggling in the lower half of the table,
seemed capable of notching up their first away win of the season --
they are the only club in the league not to have won away this
term.
</P>
<P>
But Coventry's Scottish defender Colin Hendry put the ball into
his own net in the 53rd minute as Chelsea picked up their game in
the second half.
</P>
<P>
Just five minutes later Italian striker Gianfranco Zola struck
the crucial winner which helped Chelsea to replace their London
rivals Arsenal in fourth with 58 points.
</P>
<P>
In the tight battle for Champions League places next season
Chelsea are now two points behind third-place Leeds United and
four points behind second-placed Liverpool.
</P>
<P>
Reigning champions Manchester United have a massive 11-point
lead over Liverpool at the top.
</P>
<P>
Fifth-placed Arsenal are one point behind Chelsea but have a
game in hand.
</P>
<P>
Relegation-threatened Sheffield Wednesday secured three vital
points with a 2-0 victory at lowly Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
A 39th-minute goal from Belgian international striker Gilles De
Bilde helped Wednesday on their way before Gerald Sibon scored a
second in the 88th.
</P>
<P>
The defeat puts pressure on Wimbledon who are just above the
relegation zone.
</P>
<P>
Paulo Wanchope scored two second-half goals, including an 89th-
minute winner, to help West Ham to a 2-1 defeat of Newcastle
United in London.
</P>
<P>
Gary Speed gave Newcastle the lead in the 48th minute but
Wanchope equalized for the Londoners in the 60th before hitting
the dramatic winner to help the Londoners move up one place to
eighth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
