<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weizman Calls for Greater China Role in Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Israeli President Ezer Weizman
Wednesday called on China to play a more important role in
promoting the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
"We expect China, a very important and responsible country which
aims at peace and stability in the world and has good relations
with all the countries in the Middle East, to assist in encouraging
the process," Weizman said at a dinner in honor of visiting Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is paying a state visit to Israel beginning Wednesday, the
first visit by a Chinese president to the country.
</P>
<P>
Weizman noted Jiang's visit takes place at a time when efforts
are being made to further the Middle East peace process on its
various tracks, citing intensive negotiations between Israel and
the Palestinians, Syria and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that, in the not too distant future, we will be able
to achieve a comprehensive peace with all our neighbors and I will
do all in my ability to ensure this," Weizman said.
</P>
<P>
Israel is the first leg of Jiang's five-nation visit, which will
also take him to Palestine, Turkey, Greece and South Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
