<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Protecting Turkish Nationals in Britain Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem
has urged British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook to take measures to
protect Turkish nationals residing in Britain, reported the
Anatolia News Agency on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The strong request came following the recent attacks against
Turks living in Britain, an apparent retaliation for the killing of
two British Leeds United soccer fans in Istanbul last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The two Leeds United supporters died of stab wounds as violent
clashes erupted with fans of rival Turkish team Galatasaray.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Cook, Cem expressed his sorrow at the regrettable
incidents which took place before the first leg of the UEFA
semifinals between the Turkish Galatasaray and Leeds United in
Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed Turkey's extreme unease at the racially
motivated attacks against Turkish citizens, stressing that Turkey
expects the British authorities to take all necessary measures to
prevent any repetition of such incidents.
</P>
<P>
Cem argued that the Turkish authorities had acted immediately
following the incident to bring the culprits to justice.
</P>
<P>
He noted in his letter that the general feeling of goodwill and
friendship between the peoples of the two countries must be
preserved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
