<HEADLINE> Italy Reiterates Debt Cancellation to Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a conference panel titled "Summits, compromises and
cooperation," Danielli made public his governments announcement to
cancel over 2.5 billion US dollars of foreign debt to Third World
countries.
</P>
<P>
In this amount Mozambique's debt to Italy is included.
Mozambique has been recently hit by serious flooding, with a great
number of casualties and material loss, which caused international
help to be asked for.
</P>
<P>
As an answer to this situation, Italy decided to cancel the
total amount of this African nation's commercial re-structurable
total debt amount, before the Paris Club, according to Danielli,
received favorably Italy's decision.
</P>
<P>
The multilateral financial institution, on the other hand, will
suspend Mozambique's debt payments, as a first step towards a
definitive debt cancellation, said the Vice Foreign Minister.
</P>
<P>
In spite of the Paris Club's objection to this decision, the
Italian official said that Italy is ready to act unilaterally.
</P>
<P>
According to Danielli, the Italian initiative, is among the
efforts of the South Summit, which is taking place here, with the
participation of 122 developing countries, which are asking the
rich North for a financial relief and a possible debt elimination.
</P>
<P>
As the Cuban President, Fidel Castro said during the Summit's
opening, asserted Danielli, "foreign debt is one of the main
obstacles for poor countries' development."  
</P>
</TEXT>
