<HEADLINE> UNDP Calls to Guarantee South Nations' Access to Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) Thursday made a call to industrialized nations to
guarantee commercial access to South countries' products fee of
tariffs and quotas.
</P>
<P>
UNDP Director Mallock Brown said that within the frame of the
South Summit, at Havana, a project of his organization pretends to
reduce poverty levels in 50 percent by the year 2015 in South
nations.
</P>
<P>
The official said that in order to achieve this goal it is
important that countries reach an yearly per capita economic
growth in the order of 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Brown said that UNDP will help in every possible way when
necessary to achieve that goal, but asks, at the same time to
improve national government and legislative institutions'
performance.
</P>
<P>
The Group of 77 Summit will deal, among other issues, with
poverty faced by South countries amidst globalization.  
